    "lead_finding": "Under Trump, detention is near-universal (90.0% vs 61.3% under Biden) and the release valve has nearly closed: arrests ending in swift release (no book-in) fell from 38.7% to 10.0%. Open-ended custody (booked in, not yet released) rose from 0.4% to 14.2% of detainees, with more stints per person (2 → 3). What changed is not how long or how fast ICE detains (median stay ~21.9 days, book-in within a day in both eras) but whether anyone is let go."
